---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '@/components/Nav.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About SysDesignWiki - Practical System Design Learning"
  description="SysDesignWiki helps engineers learn architecture judgment through system design concepts, capability guides, cost drivers, cloud constraints, failure modes, and case studies."
>
  <Nav />

  <main class="pt-16">
    <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-16 pb-20">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-accent mb-2">About</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-ink mb-8">SysDesign<span class="text-accent">Wiki</span></h1>

      <div class="prose-custom space-y-6 text-ink-light leading-relaxed">
        <p class="text-lg">
          SysDesignWiki is a practical learning resource for engineers who want to understand how software systems
          are shaped by tradeoffs, costs, cloud constraints, failure modes, and operational reality.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-ink pt-4">Why This Exists</h2>
        <p>
          Most system design learning either stays too theoretical or jumps straight into hyperscale architecture
          theater. This site focuses on the middle ground: the mental models that help engineers reason about
          practical 0->1 designs, understand what breaks first, and know what to measure before adding complexity.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-ink pt-4">What Each Guide Teaches</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 list-none pl-0">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-accent mt-2.5 shrink-0"></span>
            <span><strong class="text-ink">Starting designs</strong> - the simplest serious version of a capability</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-accent mt-2.5 shrink-0"></span>
            <span><strong class="text-ink">Tradeoffs</strong> - what each choice gives up, not just what it enables</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-accent mt-2.5 shrink-0"></span>
            <span><strong class="text-ink">Cost drivers</strong> - the meters and usage patterns that make systems expensive</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-accent mt-2.5 shrink-0"></span>
            <span><strong class="text-ink">Failure modes</strong> - the common ways designs degrade under real pressure</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-accent mt-2.5 shrink-0"></span>
            <span><strong class="text-ink">Cloud mappings</strong> - how provider services shape otherwise logical architecture</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-accent mt-2.5 shrink-0"></span>
            <span><strong class="text-ink">Breakpoints</strong> - the signals that tell a team when the starting design needs to evolve</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-accent mt-2.5 shrink-0"></span>
            <span><strong class="text-ink">Evidence and assumptions</strong> - what is known, inferred, simplified, or intentionally out of scope</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-ink pt-4">Scope & Methodology</h2>
        <p>
          SysDesignWiki is learning-first. It does not claim to prescribe exact production architectures,
          exact costs, provider quota guarantees, or the private internals of large companies. Case studies
          are treated as learning models based on public information and architectural inference.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-ink pt-4">Technology</h2>
        <p>
          This site is built with <strong class="text-ink">Astro</strong> and styled with
          <strong class="text-ink">Tailwind CSS v4</strong>. Architecture diagrams are rendered using
          <strong class="text-ink">Mermaid.js</strong> with a custom theme to match the editorial aesthetic.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer class="border-t border-border bg-paper-warm">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-10 text-center">
      <p class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-ink mb-2">SysDesign<span class="text-accent">Wiki</span></p>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted">Practical system design learning for tradeoffs, costs, and engineering judgment.</p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>
